verbose_text: In contrast, Bennasser et al. reported that HIV-1 gives rise to an siRNA that can inhibit HIV-1 replication, and additionally proposed that the HIV-1 Tat protein relieves this inhibition by blocking the function of the cellular Dicer, which plays a key role in both siRNA and miRNA biogenesis.
evidence: Tat protein relieves this inhibition by blocking the function of the cellular Dicer
